content.text:
The record has no `id` field! The `put` method in InMemoryStore uses `record.id || record.key` — since there's no `id`, it stores under `undefined`. But `getAll` still returns it. The issue is in `getScore`:

```js
async getScore(userId) {
    return this._reputationScoreRepo.getByUserId(userId);
}
```

This returns an **array**, not a single record. But `isRestricted` does `if (!record) return false` — an array is truthy even if empty. And `record.score` on an array is `undefined`, so `undefined < 60` is `false`.

The fix is `getScore` should return a single record:

